Kiwa Express recently opened in Ayala Malls Manila Bay offering authentic, premium and affordables Korean cuisine. 

The quick-service casual Korean restaurant is an offshoot of Kiwa Korean Grill at Solaire Resort, promising to bring premium Korean menu offerings not yet offered by any other Korean restaurants.

There has been a growing demand from Filipino regulars wanting easier access to my authentic Korean food as per Dr. David Shim, CEO and owner of Kiwa Express. It is true-to-heart Korean food. Not fusion. Not localized. The unapologetic authenticity of his food is the key to his success. 

@kiwaexpress / @kiwakoreangrill menu features items hand-picked by Dr. Shim and classified as Kiwa signature dishes or chef’s special recommendations. It’s also highly recommended to try Kimchi Jjigae - a warming, spicy stew highlighting their signature kimchi, Doenjang Jjigae, Jap Chae, and Shrimp Tempura. 

Portion sizes in Kiwa Express are priced according to individual servings. There are also family-sized options for diners who come in big groups. Packaged meal sets are offered to make ordering easier for customers.

Korean food offers a healthy alternative as it uses generous portions of vegetables. Kiwa Korean food, in particular, is not instant nor ready-made food, and always delivered via on-site preparation and cooking. I hope to provide healthier alternative for Filipino people for better well-being. 

Kiwa Express is located at the 3rd floor, Building B, Ayala Malls Manila Bay, Macapagal Boulevard corner Aseana Avenue, Paranaque City. For inquiries, guests can call +63270047472 or send a message via Instagram (https://www.instagram.com/kiwaexpress/) and Facebook (https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100089962269105).
